                <note rend="inline" type="source">662.6331/273: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Austria</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Swift</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vienna</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-08-31T16:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 31, 1931—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 31—3:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>100. The Legation has been informed by the French Minister that Vice Chancellor
                    Schober, prior to his departure to attend the League meeting at Geneva, stated
                    that the Austrian Government had decided to abandon the idea of a customs union
                    with Germany in view of prevailing conditions in Europe and that the League of
                    Nations would be notified. The Austrian Government desires that a similar
                    declaration be made by Germany.</p>
                <p>Rumor has it that on returning from the meeting at Geneva, Schober will resign
                    his place in the Cabinet for the reason that his position will be decidedly
                    weakened without the support of the pan-German element. It is also rumored that
                        Seipel<note n="23" xml:id="d444fn23">Dr. Ignaz Seipel.</note> will probably
                    succeed him.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Swift</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
